Note:
Indirect function call primitives.

This module provides the real assembly-level indirect-call helpers used by
higher-level subsystems (streams, database driver dispatch, task runtime,
async sinks, etc.) to invoke a function pointer that was supplied by the
caller. The stage1 compiler does not natively support calling an Integer
that holds a function address, so we drop to inline assembly that:

    1. Loads the function pointer (parameter 0) into rax.
    2. Reloads the remaining parameters into the System V x86_64 calling
       convention argument registers (rdi, rsi, rdx, rcx, r8, r9).
    3. Issues `call rax`, which performs the indirect branch.
    4. Stores the returned value (already in rax per the ABI) into the
       result local's stack slot, which the trailing `Return result` then
       returns through the codegen's normal epilogue.

The Intel-syntax / AT&T-syntax dialect switch is emitted explicitly inside
each block so the surrounding compiler-emitted AT&T text is not disturbed.

Stage1 stack-frame layout (verified empirically against runac_92):

    Function takes N parameters, then declares 1 local "result":
        parameter 0      -> [rbp - 8]
        parameter 1      -> [rbp - 16]
        ...
        parameter N-1    -> [rbp - N*8]
        result local     -> [rbp - (N+1)*8]

These primitives cover arities 0 through 6, which exhausts every direct
call site currently emitted by the streams, database and task subsystems
(arity 1, 2, 3, 5 are in active use; 0, 4, 6 are provided for future
callbacks without further re-implementation).

x86_64 only at this version. Cross-platform variants (arm64, riscv, etc.)
will be added under platform/<arch>/call_indirect.runa when the codegen
back-ends gain those targets; at that point this file will fan out via
the same dispatch pattern as compiler/frontend/primitives/assembly/atomic.runa.
:End Note

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Arity 0 — call fn() with no arguments
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "call_indirect_0" takes fn as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parameter 0 (fn) lives at [rbp-8]; result local lives at [rbp-16].
    Note: The function pointer is loaded into rax, then `call rax` performs
    Note: the indirect branch. The callee returns through rax per System V,
    Note: which we then save to result's slot before the normal Return path.
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        mov rax, qword ptr [rbp-8]
        call rax
        mov qword ptr [rbp-16], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Arity 1 — call fn(a)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "call_indirect_1" takes fn as Integer, a as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: fn at [rbp-8], a at [rbp-16], result at [rbp-24].
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        mov rax, qword ptr [rbp-8]
        mov rdi, qword ptr [rbp-16]
        call rax
        mov qword ptr [rbp-24], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Arity 2 — call fn(a, b)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "call_indirect_2" takes fn as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: fn at [rbp-8], a at [rbp-16], b at [rbp-24], result at [rbp-32].
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        mov rax, qword ptr [rbp-8]
        mov rdi, qword ptr [rbp-16]
        mov rsi, qword ptr [rbp-24]
        call rax
        mov qword ptr [rbp-32], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Arity 3 — call fn(a, b, c)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "call_indirect_3" takes fn as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer, c as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: fn at [rbp-8], a at [rbp-16], b at [rbp-24], c at [rbp-32], result at [rbp-40].
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        mov rax, qword ptr [rbp-8]
        mov rdi, qword ptr [rbp-16]
        mov rsi, qword ptr [rbp-24]
        mov rdx, qword ptr [rbp-32]
        call rax
        mov qword ptr [rbp-40], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Arity 4 — call fn(a, b, c, d)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "call_indirect_4" takes fn as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer, c as Integer, d as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: fn at [rbp-8], a..d at [rbp-16] through [rbp-40], result at [rbp-48].
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        mov rax, qword ptr [rbp-8]
        mov rdi, qword ptr [rbp-16]
        mov rsi, qword ptr [rbp-24]
        mov rdx, qword ptr [rbp-32]
        mov rcx, qword ptr [rbp-40]
        call rax
        mov qword ptr [rbp-48], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Arity 5 — call fn(a, b, c, d, e)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "call_indirect_5" takes fn as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer, c as Integer, d as Integer, e as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: fn at [rbp-8], a..e at [rbp-16] through [rbp-48], result at [rbp-56].
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        mov rax, qword ptr [rbp-8]
        mov rdi, qword ptr [rbp-16]
        mov rsi, qword ptr [rbp-24]
        mov rdx, qword ptr [rbp-32]
        mov rcx, qword ptr [rbp-40]
        mov r8,  qword ptr [rbp-48]
        call rax
        mov qword ptr [rbp-56], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Arity 6 — call fn(a, b, c, d, e, f)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "call_indirect_6" takes fn as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer, c as Integer, d as Integer, e as Integer, f as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: fn at [rbp-8], a..f at [rbp-16] through [rbp-56], result at [rbp-64].
    Note: For 7 total parameters, the codegen places the 7th param (here `f`)
    Note: by reading 16(%rbp) into a local slot before the body runs; thus by
    Note: the time we execute the inline asm the value already lives at
    Note: [rbp-56] just like the other params.
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        mov rax, qword ptr [rbp-8]
        mov rdi, qword ptr [rbp-16]
        mov rsi, qword ptr [rbp-24]
        mov rdx, qword ptr [rbp-32]
        mov rcx, qword ptr [rbp-40]
        mov r8,  qword ptr [rbp-48]
        mov r9,  qword ptr [rbp-56]
        call rax
        mov qword ptr [rbp-64], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process
